	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103181259710947><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=103181259710947>RE: What beyond Darkforge?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=103181259710947#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>259 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Sep 12th 2:51 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.83]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Try the twilight sea quests only if you really hate yourself.&nbsp;&nbsp;Dificulty of the MOBs, rarity of the drops and generally low quality of the armor is really unfortunate.<br><br>Blood Ember, while nice offers no stats so comes up lacking except for a few pieces that you will keep for a while.  AC is great but effectsa are too slow to cast to be really useful.  I kept 1 bracer (free invis is always nice), I only upgraded boots when I got SS Quest (free fear is a lifesaver sometimes) and the Arms I kept for the AC (effect is worthless very fast after you can make them work).<br><br>If you look for Sentient Armor you do so for the INT mostly.  Bracers, Helm and BP are the only pieces I'd upgrade over DF.<br><br>As for the rest.  Face go for the Blackened Alloy Mask for decent AC and nice stats.  Neck either spider fur or Dragon Tooth Choker will work well, spider fur has a little more AC and STR, the Choker is a major resistance item for a long time.  Back, look for the Black Bear Pelt Cloak as an awesome back item (lower AC than some but the stats more than make up for that), or the Spider Fur Cloak if your on a budget.  For the belt there are so many to chose from it's hard to recommend anything, maybe the Smiters Girdle to start, or try and loot the no drop Hybred Belt from Maiden's Eye which rot's alot anyway.<br><br>You didn't mention shoulders, but some nice shoulders are the Thunder Etched Pauldrons, good AC and +3 sv all is nice.<br><br>But honestly, once you have almost full DF the hardest 2 items to upgrade will be BP and Legs.  Other than that you'll just run across better stuff either in the Bazaar or loot it and you'll know what to do.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 60 DE Gravelord</td></tr>
